Movie ID 0 refers to a specific movie title, which is not explicitly mentioned in the query; 
The domestic gross revenue is in dollars, but the exact currency is not explicitly mentioned; 
Weekly performances imply that each week's data is reported on a specific date.

sql:
SELECT SUM(positive_count) AS total_positive_mentions
FROM social_media_sentiment
WHERE movie_id = 1;

SELECT positive_count
FROM social_media_sentiment
WHERE movie_id = 1;

SELECT SUM(attendance) AS total_attendance
FROM showings
WHERE movie_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(sentiment_score) AS average_sentiment_score
FROM social_media_sentiment
WHERE movie_id = 0;

SELECT MAX(total_gross) AS max_total_gross
FROM box_office_performance
WHERE movie_id = 0;

SELECT total_gross
FROM box_office_performance
WHERE movie_id = 0;
